summaries.short: As Bill and Marnie brace for a dangerous midnight face-off, Sookie and Eric pledge their allegiance to the King.
summaries.full: As Bill and Marnie brace for a midnight face-off, Sookie and Eric pledge their allegiance to the King. Jason is torn between friendship and passion, and Jessica is spurned from two homes. Lafayette becomes the pawn of a tormented spirit; Tommy takes a walk in someone else's shoes; Sam contends with yet another adversary in Marcus, Luna's ex and the leader of Alcide's new pack.

summaries.short: Convalescing after her latest near-death trauma, Sookie envisions a world where there's room for both Bill and Eric.
summaries.full: Convalescing after her latest near-death trauma, Sookie envisions a world where there's room for both Bill and Eric. Jesus tries to purge the restless spirit out of Lafayette; Marcus enlists Alcide to help him deal with the Sam situation. Despite Tara and Holly's misgivings, Marnie plots her next move against the vampires, during a 'Festival of Tolerance' event at Shreveport.

summaries.short: With Marnie empowered by spirits of the dead, Bill issues an unpopular order to save vampires from the light.
summaries.full: With Marnie empowered by spirits of the dead, Bill issues an unpopular order to save vampires from the light. Eric embraces his amnesia; Luna discovers Sam's not the man she thought he was; Lafayette expands his consciousness; Pam gets a body peel; Andy's date with Holly doesn't go as planned; Jessica has doubts about her future with Hoyt; Alcide and Debbie join a new pack.

summaries.full: As all hell breaks loose in Shreveport, Sookie summons her most potent powers yet to save Bill, in the process breaking a spell and leading Marnie/Antonia to re-evaluate her mission. Later, Jesus, Sookie, Lafayette and Jason try to breach the Moongoddess Emporium's defenses to liberate Tara and Holly, while Bill leads a brigade of vampires committed to destroying the place.
